    <div class="hci-badge">
        <strong>Design A: Task-Oriented Interface</strong>
        <br><br>
        <strong>HCI Principles Applied:</strong><br>
        ‚Ä¢ <em>Recognition over Recall</em> (Nielsen, 1994) - Task cards let users select intent<br>
        ‚Ä¢ <em>Visibility of System Status</em> (Nielsen, 1994) - Source badges show connections<br>
        ‚Ä¢ <em>Reduce Memory Load</em> (Shneiderman, 2016) - Examples provided<br><br>
        <strong>Data Justification:</strong> 53% of queries are ‚â§2 words; users don't know what to type
    </div>
    
    <!-- 
    ACADEMIC REFERENCES FOR THIS DESIGN:
    
    1. Nielsen, J. (1994). Enhancing the explanatory power of usability heuristics. 
       Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems (CHI '94), 152-158.
       DOI: https://doi.org/10.1145/191666.191729
       
    2. Nielsen, J., & Molich, R. (1990). Heuristic evaluation of user interfaces. 
       Proceedings of CHI '90, 249-256.
       
    3. Shneiderman, B., Plaisant, C., Cohen, M., Jacobs, S., Elmqvist, N., & Diakopoulos, N. (2016). 
       Designing the User Interface: Strategies for Effective Human-Computer Interaction (6th Edition). 
       Pearson. http://www.cs.umd.edu/hcil/DTUI6
       
    4. Norman, D. A. (2013). The Design of Everyday Things (Revised Edition). Basic Books.
    
    DESIGN JUSTIFICATION:
    - Task cards implement "Recognition over Recall" (Nielsen's Heuristic #6)
    - Three task types derived from query pattern analysis: 42% keyword, 23% question, 11% code lookup
    - Source badges implement "Visibility of System Status" (Nielsen's Heuristic #1)
    - Example queries reduce cognitive load (Shneiderman's Golden Rule #8)
    -->
    
    <script>
        function selectTask(element, type) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.task-card').forEach(card => card.classList.remove('active'));
            element.classList.add('active');
            
            const searchInput = document.getElementById('search-input');
            const searchMode = document.getElementById('search-mode');
            const suggestions = document.getElementById('suggestions');
            
            if (type === 'question') {
                searchMode.textContent = 'Questions';
                searchInput.placeholder = 'What would you like to know?';
                suggestions.innerHTML = `
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">What is the FIN of HUDC on single aisle?</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">How to justify a load increase?</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">Where is the ps3 template?</span>
                `;
            } else if (type === 'document') {
                searchMode.textContent = 'Documents';
                searchInput.placeholder = 'Enter keywords or topic...';
                suggestions.innerHTML = `
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">A350 RSDP design principles</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">edge distance requirements</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip">spigot loads A320</span>
                `;
            } else if (type === 'lookup') {
                searchMode.textContent = 'ID Lookup';
                searchInput.placeholder = 'Enter document ID (e.g., UG2300123, ATA 2372)';
                suggestions.innerHTML = `
                    <span class="suggestion-chip code">UG2300123</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip code">ATA 2372</span>
                    <span class="suggestion-chip code">M2943</span>
                `;
            }
        }
        
        // Make suggestion chips clickable
        document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
            if (e.target.classList.contains('suggestion-chip')) {
                document.getElementById('search-input').value = e.target.textContent;
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
